      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "Are we sure this is completely fixed? In particular, my reasoning is that key `GetPubKey()`:line30 might not be thread safe, since `GetPubKey()` uses `secp256k1_context_sign`:key.cpp:line16, which is a global variable. It seems to me that any concurrent reading and writing will result in a race condition of one kind or another. I might well be wrong about this particular example, but I think we should be sure of the fact that `GetPubKey()` and whatever it happens to call is thread safe.\n",
